Sec. 60.102. REPAYMENT OF ORGANIZATIONAL EXPENSES. The
directors may pay:
(1) all costs and expenses necessarily incurred in the
creation and organization of the district;
(2) the cost of investigation and making plans, including
the cost of feasibility analyses, engineering reports, design fees,
and other necessary costs; and
(3) legal fees.
Added by Acts 2001, 77th Leg., ch. 1393, Sec. 1, eff. June 16, 2001.

